Ajax confirmed the departure of Tendai Ndoro from the club, stating that his contract was up for renewal at the end of June, but the club opted against extending his stay at Ikamva. JOHANNESBURG - Relegated Cape Town outfit, Ajax Cape Town, have released striker Tendai Ndoro just six months after signing with the club. Ajax, who docked points for illegally fielding Ndoro in the past season, saw themselves eventually being relegated from the Absa Premiership. Ndoro had represented three clubs in one season, which is against the Fifa rules. Ajax confirmed the departure of Ndoro from the club, stating that his contract was up for renewal at the end of June, but the club opted against extending his stay at Ikamva.